<h4 class="toc__title">John Epistles Study Notes<br /><span style="font-size: 0.6em; color: rgb(159, 29, 33);">
<a href="{{ site.url }}/bible-studies-viet/Tho-Giang/"><em>(<u>Bấm vào đây để đọc tiếng Việt</u>)</em></a></span>
</h4>
<ul class="toc__menu" id="markdown-toc">
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch1-ch2-v6/"><u>1 John 1-2:6</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">If we walk in the light. To know God is to keep his commandments. To abide in Christ is to walk just as Jesus walked.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch2-v7-27/"><u>1 John 2:7-27</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">The old commandment. Definition of love.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch2-v28-ch3-v10/"><u>1 John 2:28-3:10</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Remain in Him. Purify himself. Everyone who resides in Him does not sin. So it is with the one who does not love his fellow Christians.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch3-v11-21/"><u>1 John 3:11-21</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Not like Cain. The one who does not love remains in death. Conscience condemned vs. confident.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch3-v22-24/"><u>1 John 3:22-24</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Whatever we ask. Another gospel?</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch4-v1-11/"><u>1 John 4:1-11</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Do not believe every spirit. The person who does not love does not know God.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch4-v12-21/"><u>1 John 4:12-21</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">If we love one another. By this we know. If anyone confesses. Confidence in the day of judgement.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch5-v1-3/"><u>1 John 5:1-3</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Old commandment: love one another. New commandment: Believe in Christ.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch5-v4-13/"><u>1 John 5:4-13</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">The conquering power. Testimony concerning Jesus Christ.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/john-epistles/1John-ch5-v14-21/"><u>1 John 5:14-21</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Whatever we ask. Sin not unto death. Christians don’t sin. We vs. the whole world. Insight to know God. Guard yourself from idols.</span></li>
</ul>
</nav>
